---
import ToolLayout from '../../layouts/ToolLayout.astro';
---

<ToolLayout
  title="QR Code Generator"
  description="Generate QR codes from URLs or text for free. Customize size, colors, and download as PNG. No sign-up required."
>
  <div id="qr-app">
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div>
        <label for="qr-input" class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-1">URL or Text</label>
        <textarea
          id="qr-input"
          rows="3"
          placeholder="Enter a URL or text to generate a QR code..."
          class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg p-3 text-base resize-y focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-indigo-500 focus:border-transparent"
        >https://example.com</textarea>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
        <div>
          <label for="qr-size" class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-1">Size</label>
          <select id="qr-size" class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg p-2 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-indigo-500">
            <option value="5">Small (150px)</option>
            <option value="8" selected>Medium (240px)</option>
            <option value="12">Large (360px)</option>
          </select>
        </div>
        <div>
          <label for="qr-fg" class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-1">Foreground Color</label>
          <input type="color" id="qr-fg" value="#000000" class="w-full h-10 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg cursor-pointer" />
        </div>
        <div>
          <label for="qr-bg" class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-1">Background Color</label>
          <input type="color" id="qr-bg" value="#ffffff" class="w-full h-10 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg cursor-pointer" />
        </div>
      </div>

      <button id="qr-generate" class="bg-indigo-600 text-white px-6 py-2 rounded-lg text-sm hover:bg-indigo-700 transition-colors">
        Generate QR Code
      </button>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col items-center">
      <canvas id="qr-canvas" class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg" style="display:none;"></canvas>
      <button id="qr-download" class="mt-4 bg-green-600 text-white px-6 py-2 rounded-lg text-sm hover:bg-green-700 transition-colors" style="display:none;">
        Download PNG
      </button>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- SEO Content -->
  <div class="mt-12 prose prose-sm max-w-none">
    <h2>Free Online QR Code Generator</h2>
    <p>Create QR codes instantly from any URL or text. Our free QR code maker online lets you customize colors and sizes, then download as a high-quality PNG image. Perfect for business cards, marketing materials, event tickets, and more.</p>

    <h3>Features</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Instant generation</strong> - Generate QR codes in seconds</li>
      <li><strong>Custom colors</strong> - Choose your own foreground and background colors</li>
      <li><strong>Multiple sizes</strong> - Small, medium, or large output</li>
      <li><strong>PNG download</strong> - Save your QR code as a high-quality image</li>
      <li><strong>No sign-up required</strong> - Completely free QR code generator</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>How to Use</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Enter a URL or text in the input field</li>
      <li>Customize the size and colors as needed</li>
      <li>Click "Generate QR Code" to create your code</li>
      <li>Download the QR code as a PNG image</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <div class="mt-12 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Is this QR code generator really free?</summary>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 text-sm">Yes, our QR code generator is completely free to use with no sign-up or account required. You can generate unlimited QR codes, customize colors and sizes, and download them as PNG images at no cost.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Do the QR codes expire?</summary>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 text-sm">No, QR codes generated with this tool are static and never expire. The data is encoded directly into the QR code image, so it will work as long as the URL or content it points to remains available.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">What can I encode in a QR code?</summary>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 text-sm">You can encode any text or URL into a QR code. Common uses include website links, email addresses, phone numbers, Wi-Fi credentials, and plain text messages. The maximum content length depends on the complexity of the data.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Can I use generated QR codes for commercial purposes?</summary>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 text-sm">Absolutely. QR codes generated with this tool are yours to use however you like, including on business cards, product packaging, marketing flyers, and restaurant menus. There are no usage restrictions.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Why is my QR code not scanning?</summary>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 text-sm">Make sure there is enough contrast between the foreground and background colors. Dark foreground on a light background works best. Also ensure the QR code is printed or displayed at a large enough size for your scanner to read it clearly.</p>
    </details>
  </div>
</ToolLayout>

<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/qrcode-generator@1.4.4/qrcode.min.js"></script>
<script>
  const input = document.getElementById('qr-input') as HTMLTextAreaElement;
  const sizeSelect = document.getElementById('qr-size') as HTMLSelectElement;
  const fgColor = document.getElementById('qr-fg') as HTMLInputElement;
  const bgColor = document.getElementById('qr-bg') as HTMLInputElement;
  const generateBtn = document.getElementById('qr-generate')!;
  const canvas = document.getElementById('qr-canvas') as HTMLCanvasElement;
  const downloadBtn = document.getElementById('qr-download')!;

  function generateQR() {
    const text = input.value.trim();
    if (!text) return;

    const cellSize = parseInt(sizeSelect.value);
    const qr = (window as any).qrcode(0, 'M');
    qr.addData(text);
    qr.make();

    const moduleCount = qr.getModuleCount();
    const margin = 4;
    const size = (moduleCount + margin * 2) * cellSize;

    canvas.width = size;
    canvas.height = size;
    const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d')!;

    ctx.fillStyle = bgColor.value;
    ctx.fillRect(0, 0, size, size);

    ctx.fillStyle = fgColor.value;
    for (let row = 0; row < moduleCount; row++) {
      for (let col = 0; col < moduleCount; col++) {
        if (qr.isDark(row, col)) {
          ctx.fillRect(
            (col + margin) * cellSize,
            (row + margin) * cellSize,
            cellSize,
            cellSize
          );
        }
      }
    }

    canvas.style.display = 'block';
    downloadBtn.style.display = 'inline-block';
  }

  generateBtn.addEventListener('click', generateQR);

  downloadBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
    const link = document.createElement('a');
    link.download = 'qrcode.png';
    link.href = canvas.toDataURL('image/png');
    link.click();
  });

  // Generate on load
  generateQR();
</script>
